# Dense-edge stiffness diagnostic: is the hang f_kappa-driven, or a solver issue at extreme density?
# small_dense_highsfe (nCore 1e6) -- the config whose live ebpeak runs HUNG (cal_dense__ek*). All knobs
# DEFAULT (cooling_boost_kappa=1.0, transition_trigger=cooling_balance), so this is the pure baseline;
# the ONLY variable across the pair is betadelta_solver. The committed cleanroom frozen data (165 rows,
# completed) was a LEGACY rerun -- hypothesis: hybr (the new default) is the one that stalls here.
model_name      diag_dense_hybr
path2output     outputs/kcal/diag_dense_hybr
mCloud    1e4
nCore    1e6
rCore    0.1
sfe    0.5
dens_profile    densPL
densPL_alpha    0
betadelta_solver    hybr
log_console    False
log_file    True
stop_t    0.1
